<div id="review_2140363950" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2140363950" />
    <a title="Darkowaa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24659898-darkowaa"><img alt="Darkowaa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1528929840p2/24659898.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2140363950?book_show_action=true">Oct 03, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Darkowaa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Darkowaa" href="/user/show/24659898-darkowaa">Darkowaa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2140363950" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12452524976582105206">One of the best books I’ve read this year. ‘Our Sister Killjoy’ has managed to fill the void I’ve been battling/constantly grappling with, wrt my conflicting feelings on ‘Afropolitanism’, 1st gen Americans, living abroad, assimilation, ‘the real African’, moving back to the continent &amp; the ‘savior’ mentality the ‘been-tos’ bring, feminism, loneliness. <br/>A LOT is explored in this short book and its fucking golden. I wish I read this earlier in my life.<br/>I don’t know if I can even write a full review </span>
  <span id="freeText12452524976582105206" style="display:none">One of the best books I’ve read this year. ‘Our Sister Killjoy’ has managed to fill the void I’ve been battling/constantly grappling with, wrt my conflicting feelings on ‘Afropolitanism’, 1st gen Americans, living abroad, assimilation, ‘the real African’, moving back to the continent &amp; the ‘savior’ mentality the ‘been-tos’ bring, feminism, loneliness. <br />A LOT is explored in this short book and its fucking golden. I wish I read this earlier in my life.<br />I don’t know if I can even write a full review on this book, but once I let it marinate in my mind and heart, I surely will. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12452524976582105206" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
