<div id="review_1610014354" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1610014354" />
    <a title="Maria Longley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16558598-maria-longley"><img alt="Maria Longley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1358510038p2/16558598.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1610014354?book_show_action=true">Jun 16, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maria Longley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maria Longley" href="/user/show/16558598-maria-longley">Maria Longley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16558598-maria-longley?shelf=fa">fa</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16558598-maria-longley?shelf=2018">2018</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1610014354" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14286568835332734589">Sissie, the student protagonist of this prose-poetry novel(la), is a Ghanian exploring Germany, England and Europe on a sponsored visit and her experiences as a traveller in the &quot;civilised world&quot; of colonisers of the African continent. Ama Ata Aidoo explores Europe as a place of exile for Sissie, somewhere to report back from, somewhere that isn&apos;t the idealised place &quot;West&quot; that is held up/onto by many back home. This was published in 1977 although written years earlier.</span>
  <span id="freeText14286568835332734589" style="display:none">Sissie, the student protagonist of this prose-poetry novel(la), is a Ghanian exploring Germany, England and Europe on a sponsored visit and her experiences as a traveller in the "civilised world" of colonisers of the African continent. Ama Ata Aidoo explores Europe as a place of exile for Sissie, somewhere to report back from, somewhere that isn't the idealised place "West" that is held up/onto by many back home. This was published in 1977 although written years earlier.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14286568835332734589" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


